article.headline: Indiana St. 65, Colorado St. 60
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Sophomore Dwayne Lathan posted team-leading totals of 18 points and nine rebounds as Indiana State defeated Colorado State 65-60 on Friday night. Harry Marshall scored 15 points for the Sycamores (3-1), and Jake Kelly added 13 in a game that was part of the inaugural Mountain West/Missouri Valley Conference Challenge. The Rams (2-2) were led by Dorian Green's 18 points. Andy Ogide added 12 and Andre McFarland 11. The game was tied 29-29 at the half, but Indiana State used a 7-0 spurt to gain a 36-29 edge before Colorado State rallied midway through the second half to lead 40-39 on Travis Franklin's layup. Latham sank two free throws made it 41-40, and the Sycamores never trailed after that. Indiana State held advantages of 34-32 in rebounds, 9-8 in assists, 5-0 in blocks and 17-13 in turnovers.
